 the treatment of bipolar disorder, mania, and depression. It was first proposed for psychiatric use by Cade in 1949 and has since become a cornerstone in managing mood disorders. Lithium is particularly effective in preventing suicide in patients with depression and in stabilizing manic episodes. However, its use requires careful monitoring of blood levels to avoid toxicity, as it can cause severe adverse reactions, including malignant syndrome. Despite its potential risks, lithium remains a widely utilized and essential medication in the management of mood disorders.", "硝苯呋海因:硝苯呋海因被认为是木僵缄默综合征的特效药物之一，用于治疗该综合征。", "溴隐亭:溴隐亭被认为是木僵缄默综合征的特效药物之一，用于治疗该综合征。"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}